{"article_id":"YBfj8k7v8MsjyhBh","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"Yuck .","depth":4},{"id":1,"text":"The jobs market lost some steam in August ,","depth":8},{"id":2,"text":"with only 142,000 jobs added last month .","depth":8},{"id":3,"text":"The consensus forecast from economists","depth":9},{"id":4,"text":"surveyed by CNNMoney","depth":9},{"id":5,"text":"was for a jobs gain of 226,000 jobs .","depth":8},{"id":6,"text":"The unemployment rate dipped slightly to 6.1 % , down from 6.2 % in July .","depth":8},{"id":7,"text":"That was in line with estimates ,","depth":9},{"id":8,"text":"but it was n't much for job seekers","depth":10},{"id":9,"text":"to celebrate .","depth":10},{"id":10,"text":"This breaks a streak of six straight months with more than 200,000 jobs added .","depth":7},{"id":11,"text":"It may raise questions about the strength of the job market 's rebound .","depth":6},{"id":12,"text":"Many Americans already do not feel","depth":8},{"id":13,"text":"that the job market has fully recovered from the Great Recession .","depth":8},{"id":14,"text":"CNN 's Christine Romans hosts Facebook chat with Labor Secretary Thomas Perez","depth":8},{"id":15,"text":"Federal Reserve chair Janet Yellen has also repeatedly stressed","depth":9},{"id":16,"text":"that the labor market could be stronger .","depth":9},{"id":17,"text":"Friday 's numbers are unlikely to change the Fed 's decision","depth":6},{"id":18,"text":"to keep a key short-term rate at historic lows for the foreseeable future in an effort","depth":7},{"id":19,"text":"to stimulate more job growth .","depth":7},{"id":20,"text":"That appears to be what Wall Street is counting on","depth":7},{"id":21,"text":"-- stocks were relatively flat Friday .","depth":8},{"id":22,"text":"The yield on the 10-year U.S. Treasury dipped as well , a sign","depth":9},{"id":23,"text":"that the bond market does not believe","depth":10},{"id":24,"text":"the Fed is going to make any big moves just yet .","depth":10},{"id":25,"text":"`` Yellen is looking at trends .","depth":9},{"id":26,"text":"The Fed is not going to be terribly reactive to one month of data , ''","depth":9},{"id":27,"text":"said Chris Molumphy , chief investment officer of Franklin Templeton Fixed Income Group .","depth":8},{"id":28,"text":"He added","depth":8},{"id":29,"text":"that there would need to be at least two more months of subpar jobs growth","depth":9},{"id":30,"text":"before the Fed","depth":11},{"id":31,"text":"-- and consumers and investors --","depth":11},{"id":32,"text":"should be worried about the economy .","depth":10},{"id":33,"text":"But it 's not all bad news .","depth":5},{"id":34,"text":"The economy has averaged nearly 220,000 jobs added a month ,","depth":7},{"id":35,"text":"and the payroll gains were revised higher for both June and July .","depth":7},{"id":36,"text":"One expert said","depth":9},{"id":37,"text":"that it 's important to remember that the August number could eventually change as well","depth":10},{"id":38,"text":"-- for the better .","depth":10},{"id":39,"text":"`` This number will be revised higher .","depth":11},{"id":40,"text":"August is the quirkiest month , ''","depth":11},{"id":41,"text":"said Phil Orlando , chief equity strategist with Federated Investors .","depth":10},{"id":42,"text":"`` This is inconsistent with strength","depth":10},{"id":43,"text":"we 're seeing elsewhere in the economy . ''","depth":10},{"id":44,"text":"Recall","depth":9},{"id":45,"text":"that the government originally reported","depth":10},{"id":46,"text":"that zero","depth":12},{"id":47,"text":"( that 's right , zilch )","depth":12},{"id":48,"text":"new jobs were added in August 2011 .","depth":11},{"id":49,"text":"The number wound up getting revised sharply higher a couple of months later .","depth":8},{"id":50,"text":"Beyond the headlines :","depth":4},{"id":51,"text":"Hourly wages rose slightly .","depth":5},{"id":52,"text":"They are up 2.1 % over the past 12 months .","depth":6},{"id":53,"text":"However , that 's only slightly higher than the inflation rate .","depth":7},{"id":54,"text":"So workers wo n't feel much better off .","depth":7},{"id":55,"text":"There were solid job gains in several industries","depth":8},{"id":56,"text":"that tend to pay well ,","depth":8},{"id":57,"text":"such as business and professional services and health care .","depth":7},{"id":58,"text":"Jobs were added in the construction sector as well , a possible sign","depth":7},{"id":59,"text":"that the housing market is continuing to bounce back .","depth":7},{"id":60,"text":"John Canally , chief economic strategist for LPL Financial , noted","depth":8},{"id":61,"text":"that weakness in the manufacturing and retail sectors , dragged down overall job growth .","depth":8},{"id":62,"text":"He said","depth":8},{"id":63,"text":"there may be some strange seasonal , end-of-summer factors","depth":9},{"id":64,"text":"to explain that .","depth":9},{"id":65,"text":"Related :","depth":8},{"id":66,"text":"College grads are underemployed ,","depth":9},{"id":67,"text":"but a degree is still worth it `","depth":9},{"id":68,"text":"` My view of the job market is unchanged from where it was","depth":10},{"id":69,"text":"before this report came out .","depth":10},{"id":70,"text":"This is an anomaly , ''","depth":9},{"id":71,"text":"Canally said .","depth":8},{"id":72,"text":"Still , there were other lackluster signs in the job report .","depth":5},{"id":73,"text":"The so-called `` underemployment rate , ''","depth":9},{"id":74,"text":"which counts discouraged workers","depth":11},{"id":75,"text":"who have given up looking for jobs","depth":11},{"id":76,"text":"and people","depth":12},{"id":77,"text":"working part-time","depth":12},{"id":78,"text":"who would rather have a full-time job ,","depth":11},{"id":79,"text":"is 12 % .","depth":8},{"id":80,"text":"That 's down from July","depth":8},{"id":81,"text":"but still nearly double the official unemployment rate .","depth":8},{"id":82,"text":"And the labor force participation rate ,","depth":9},{"id":83,"text":"which measures","depth":10},{"id":84,"text":"how many people of working age are actually in the job market ,","depth":10},{"id":85,"text":"remained near its lowest levels in more than 35 years .","depth":8},{"id":86,"text":"That 's a function of more and more people , particularly women and retiring baby boomers , dropping out of the work force .","depth":7},{"id":87,"text":"The political reaction :","depth":2},{"id":88,"text":"U.S. Secretary of Labor Thomas Perez noted in a statement Friday morning","depth":6},{"id":89,"text":"that the private sector has now added jobs for 54 consecutive months .","depth":6},{"id":90,"text":"That 's the longest streak ever .","depth":5},{"id":91,"text":"But he added","depth":6},{"id":92,"text":"that `` there are still 3 million long-term unemployed Americans ,","depth":7},{"id":93,"text":"and we can do more","depth":8},{"id":94,"text":"to help those","depth":9},{"id":95,"text":"who are still struggling to recover . ''","depth":9},{"id":96,"text":"He reiterated President Obama 's call to Congress","depth":6},{"id":97,"text":"to raise the minimum wage .","depth":6},{"id":98,"text":"House Speaker John Boehner did not address the minimum wage issue in his own statement .","depth":4},{"id":99,"text":"But he said","depth":5},{"id":100,"text":"Republicans in the House have `` advanced solutions","depth":7},{"id":101,"text":"to help create more jobs ,","depth":8},{"id":102,"text":"lower costs at home ,","depth":9},{"id":103,"text":"and restore opportunity for all Americans , ''","depth":9},{"id":104,"text":"but that the GOP 's plans `` have run up against a brick wall '' in the Democrat-controlled Senate .","depth":6}],"relations":[{"parent":209,"left":191,"right":208,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":191,"left":154,"right":190,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":154,"left":121,"right":153,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":121,"left":0,"right":12